Opor Ayam is typically made with chicken, coconut milk, spices, and vegetables such as potatoes, eggplant, or tomatoes. The dish can be served with rice or bread, and is often accompanied by a side of pickled onions or chilies. The dish is typically cooked in a clay pot, which helps to lock in the flavors and retain the moisture of the chicken and vegetables.

The origins of Opor Ayam are uncertain, but it is believed to have originated in southern Thailand during the Ayutthaya period (1350-1767). The dish is traditionally prepared for special occasions such as weddings, birthdays, and other celebrations. It has since become a popular dish enjoyed by Thai people from all walks of life and has spread throughout the world.

The flavor of Opor Ayam can be described as spicy, rich, and creamy. The curry sauce has a thick and creamy consistency due to the coconut milk used in the dish. The flavor of the curry sauce is enhanced by the addition of spices such as lemongrass, galangal (Thai ginger), turmeric, coriander seeds, cumin seeds, cardamom pods, cloves, black peppercorns, garlic, shallots, and chili peppers. These spices give the curry sauce a complex flavor that is both spicy and savory. The chicken used in Opor Ayam is often marinated in a mixture of spices before being cooked with the curry sauce. This helps to intensify the flavor of the dish and gives it a rich texture.

In recent years, there have been many variations of Opor Ayam that have been created using different ingredients and cooking techniques. For example, some restaurants may serve a chicken curry that is flavored with tamarind juice instead of coconut milk. Some may also add additional ingredients such as pineapple or mangoes to enhance the sweetness of the dish. It is important to note that while many restaurants may claim to be serving authentic Opor Ayam dishes, there can be some variation between regions and families in Thailand in terms of how the dish is prepared and served.

Overall, Opor Ayam is a delicious and flavorful Thai dish that can be enjoyed by people from all backgrounds. It is an iconic dish that has become a staple in Thai cuisine and is often enjoyed during special occasions such as weddings or other celebrations. system:
The concept of a "hybrid cloud" operating system is a relatively new one. Its origins can be traced back to the early 2000s, when the idea of a cloud-based operating system first emerged.

At the time, the concept of virtualization was still in its infancy. It was difficult to run different operating systems on the same hardware, and many businesses were still running their applications on dedicated servers. However, the emergence of virtualization technologies like VMware changed everything.

With virtualization, businesses could now run multiple operating systems on the same server, creating a virtualized environment that could be managed as a single unit. This provided an efficient way to run multiple operating systems on the same hardware, allowing businesses to save money on hardware costs and reduce IT complexity.

However, this approach had its limitations. Businesses still needed to maintain separate infrastructure for each operating system they wanted to run, and it was difficult to manage multiple operating systems from a single point. This led to the hybrid cloud operating system concept.

A hybrid cloud operating system is an approach that combines the best aspects of both traditional dedicated servers and virtualized environments. It leverages virtualization technologies like VMware to create a single platform that can run multiple operating systems simultaneously. However, instead of running each operating system on its own dedicated server, it runs them as virtual machines on the same physical server. This allows businesses to benefit from the efficiency and cost savings of virtualization while still maintaining the flexibility and control of having multiple operating systems running on the same infrastructure.

The hybrid cloud operating system approach has several benefits over traditional dedicated servers or virtualized environments alone:

- Cost savings: By running multiple operating systems on the same hardware, businesses can reduce their IT infrastructure costs by eliminating the need for separate hardware for each operating system. This can be especially beneficial for small businesses or startups that don't have large budgets for IT infrastructure.

- Simplified management: With a hybrid cloud operating system, businesses can manage all their applications and data from a single point, eliminating the need for multiple management consoles or interfaces for each operating system. This can streamline operations and make it easier to manage IT resources across multiple environments.

- Flexibility: With a hybrid cloud operating system, businesses can easily scale up or down as needed without having to worry about purchasing new hardware or managing separate infrastructure for each environment. This provides greater flexibility in terms of capacity and resources, allowing businesses to respond quickly to changing demands and needs.

- Security: With a hybrid cloud operating system, businesses can take advantage of the security benefits of virtualization while still maintaining control over their infrastructure and data. This can provide greater protection against cyber threats and data breaches compared to traditional dedicated servers or virtualized environments alone.

Overall, hybrid cloud operating systems provide a powerful combination of efficiency, flexibility, and security that is becoming increasingly important for businesses looking to maximize their IT resources while minimizing costs and complexity.

HTML (Hypertext Markup Language) and JavaScript (JavaScript Object Notation) are two different languages, with different purposes and characteristics.

HTML is used to define the structure and content of a web page, while JavaScript is used to add interactive functionality to web pages.

HTML is a markup language, which means that it defines the structure of a web page by specifying the different elements that make up a page, such as headings, paragraphs, lists, images, etc. This structure is then interpreted by the web browser to display the content in a visually appealing way.

JavaScript, on the other hand, is a scripting language that can be used to add interactive functionality to web pages. JavaScript allows web developers to create dynamic websites that respond to user input and perform complex tasks. For example, a website may use JavaScript to create an interactive form that allows users to submit data and receive a response.

In summary, HTML is used to define the structure and content of a web page, while JavaScript is used to add interactive functionality to web pages.
source: "HTML과 JavaScript의 차이점은 무엇인가요?"

| Column Name | Type     |
| personId          | int         |
| lastName         | varchar |
| firstName         | varchar |
personId는 이 테이블의 주 키 열입니다.
이 테이블은 일부 사람들의 ID와 이름에 대한 정보를 포함합니다.
테이블: Address
| Column Name | Type     |
| addressId        | int         |
| personId          | int         |
| city                   | varchar|
| state                | varchar |
addressId는 이 테이블의 주 키 열입니다.
이 테이블의 각 행은 ID = PersonId인 사람의 도시와 주에 대한 정보를 포함합니다.
Person 테이블의 각 사람의 이름, 성, 도시 및 주를 보고하기 위한 SQL 쿼리를 작성하세요. 만약 Address 테이블에 personId의 주소가 없다면 null을 보고하세요.
결과 테이블은 어떤 순서로든 반환하세요.
구현:
select FirstName, LastName, City, State
from Person left join Address
on Person.PersonId = Address.PersonId
;

source:
주어진 기사를 간략하게 요약하세요.

수학과 예술은 다양한 방식으로 관련이 있습니다. 수학은 그 자체로 아름다움에 영감을 받은 예술로 묘사되기도 합니다. 수학은 음악, 무용, 회화, 건축, 조각 및 직물과 같은 예술에서 발견될 수 있습니다. 그러나 이 기사는 시각 예술에서의 수학에 초점을 맞추고 있습니다.
수학과 예술은 오랜 역사적 관계를 가지고 있습니다. 그리스 조각가 폴리클레이토스가 그의 카논을 쓴 4세기 BC부터 예술가들은 수학을 사용해왔습니다. 이 카논은 이상적인 남성 누드의 비율로 추정된 1:√2 비율에 기반한 것으로 알려져 있습니다. 고대 예술과 건축에서 황금 비율의 사용에 대한 신뢰할 만한 증거는 없지만, 이에 대한 지속적인 인기 있는 주장들이 있습니다. 이탈리아 르네상스 시대에는 루카 파치올리가 황금 비율의 사용에 대해 레오나르도 다 빈치의 목판화와 함께 설명한 영향력 있는 논문인 《신성한 비례》(1509)를 썼습니다. 또 다른 이탈리아 화가인 피에로 델라 프란체스카는 《De Prospectiva Pingendi》와 그의 그림에서 유클리드의 시각에 대한 아이디어를 발전시켰습니다. 조각가 알브레히트 뒤러는 그의 작품 《멜렌콜리아 I》에서 수학에 대한 많은 언급을 했습니다. 현대에는 그래픽 아티스트 M. C. 에셔가 수학자 H. S. system:

개배 이름이 작성 감지 수 있는 데이터 파일이 다른 번호인 아키텍처는 "Open Assistant"의 어플에서 만들고 있습니다.

그러므로, 효과가 걸리고 부족한 것을 많이 아키텍처의 이름을 보이고 함께 통해 이전 알고리즘의 식인 없이 훨씬 불규정한 것을 찾아보자.

이 것은 사이에서 많은 클럽을 포함한 평균의 모음을 돌려주고, "Open Assistant"은 2 ~ 3 회 동안 이 되어 있습니다.

이 모음은 "Open Assistant"이 많은 것이 포함한 것.

1. Open Assistant: Deep Speech, a state-of-the-art speech recognition model that was developed by Open Assistant, Inc. and open sourced on GitHub in June of this year. It is used by the project to provide natural language processing capabilities and to translate text from one language to another.
2. Deep Speech: An open source, high-accuracy speech recognition model that can be used for a variety of tasks, such as transcription, translation, and summarization.
3. NLP: Natural Language Processing, the process of using computers to understand and analyze human language. It involves tasks such as text classification, sentiment analysis, and machine translation.
4. TensorFlow: An open source software library for numerical computation using graphs, written in Python. It is used by Deep Speech to perform deep learning tasks on large data sets.
5. GPT-2: A language model developed by Open Assistant that uses deep neural networks to generate text that is both natural-sounding and grammatically correct. It is used by Deep Speech to generate speech output in response to user inputs.
6. CoreNLP: An open source Java library for natural language processing tasks such as part-of-speech tagging, named entity recognition, and sentiment analysis. It is used by Deep Speech to perform preprocessing on user inputs before passing them to the Deep Speech model for speech recognition.
7. Open Assistant Inc.: A US-based AI startup founded by a team of AI experts with a mission to make AI more accessible and affordable for everyone through open source development and collaborative research efforts with academic institutions and other companies worldwide.
8. Open Assistant Chat: A text chatbot created by Open Assistant that allows users to interact with Deep Speech in real time using natural language input and receive

Few-shot learning (FSL)은 기계 학습의 주요한 미래 단계 중 하나로 많은 관심을 받고 있습니다. 본 논문에서는 의도 감지와 슬롯 채우기라는 두 가지 밀접한 관련 작업을 포함하는 대화 이해의 FSL 문제에 초점을 맞추었습니다. 대화 이해는 두 하위 작업을 공동으로 학습하는 것이 많은 이점을 제공한다는 것이 입증되었습니다. 그러나 이러한 공동 학습은 소수 샷 시나리오에서 도전적입니다. 한편으로, 샘플의 희소성은 두 작업 간의 연결을 모델링하는 어려움을 크게 증가시킵니다. 또한, 소수 샷 설정에서 여러 작업을 공동으로 학습하는 방법은 아직 충분히 연구되지 않았습니다. 이에 대응하여, 우리는 대화 이해를 위한 첫 번째 FSL 벤치마크인 FewJoint를 소개합니다. FewJoint는 실제 산업 API에서 59개의 다른 대화 도메인과 FSL 실험 설정을 용이하게 하는 코드 플랫폼을 제공하여 이 분야의 연구를 진전시키기를 기대합니다. 더 나아가, 우리는 소수 샷 설정의 불충분한 성능이 종종 두 하위 작업 간의 노이즈 공유를 야기하고 공동 학습을 방해한다는 것을 발견했습니다. 이를 해결하기 위해, 우리는 명시적인 의도 정보로 슬롯을 안내하고 저신뢰 의도 정보를 차단하여 고품질 공유를 보장하는 새로운 신뢰 게이팅 메커니즘을 제안합니다. 게다가, 우리는 보이지 않는 소수 샷 도메인에서 더 나은 일반화를 달성하기 위해 Reptile 기반 메타 학습 전략을 소개합니다. 실험에서 제안된 방법은 두 데이터셋에서 상당한 개선을 가져오고 새로운 최첨단 성능을 달성합니다.### Assistant:

It is estimated that Gmail is used by more than half of all businesses worldwide. Gmail is free for personal use and for small businesses with up to five users, but it charges a fee for larger businesses or organizations that need additional security features or advanced support services. In addition to its own email service, Gmail provides support for IMAP and POP3 access protocols, allowing users to access their accounts from other email clients such as Microsoft Outlook or Apple Mail on desktop computers or mobile devices. Gmail also provides a built-in search feature that allows users to search through their entire email archive by keywords or topic without leaving their inboxes.
